%N A385584 a(n) is the number of ways to express n as the sum of a nonnegative integer, a triangular number and a triangular pyramidal number.
%C A385584 This sequence in nondecreasing.
%H A385584 Zhi-Wei Sun, <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/0905.0635">On universal sums of polygonal numbers, preprint</a>, arXiv:0905.0635 [math.NT], 2009.
%t A385584 a[n_] := Block[{cnt = 0, triind, pyr, pyrind = Floor[N[(3n + Sqrt[9n^2 - 1/27])^(1/3) + (3n - Sqrt[9n^2 - 1/27])^(1/3) - 1]]}, While[ pyrind > -1, pyr = pyrind (pyrind + 1) (pyrind + 2)/6; triind = Floor[(Sqrt[8 (n - pyr) + 1] - 1)/2]; While[ triind > -1, If[ 2pyr + 2 > triind (triind + 1), cnt++]; triind--]; pyrind--]; cnt]; Array[a, 74, 0]
